1
00:00:12,371 --> 00:00:15,811
♪Have you ever heard about♪

2
00:00:15,811 --> 00:00:18,691
♪The cliff of a snow mountain♪

3
00:00:19,211 --> 00:00:24,331
♪Once fascinated numerous people?♪

4
00:00:26,011 --> 00:00:29,251
♪Legend has it that♪

5
00:00:29,251 --> 00:00:32,051
♪There were treasures at the peak♪

6
00:00:32,891 --> 00:00:37,971
♪But also there was a bottomless chasm
hidden over there♪

7
00:00:39,571 --> 00:00:43,011
♪The smart, the fool♪

8
00:00:43,051 --> 00:00:45,851
♪And the kind people♪

9
00:00:46,491 --> 00:00:52,331
♪All are familiar to you♪

10
00:00:53,211 --> 00:00:56,771
♪On the mountainside, on the cliff♪

11
00:00:57,091 --> 00:00:59,691
♪On the cloud♪

12
00:01:00,091 --> 00:01:05,211
♪And in the human world♪

13
00:01:17,051 --> 00:01:24,331
♪Snowflakes are drifting
profusely and disorderly♪

14
00:01:36,091 --> 00:01:40,091
=Joy of Life Special Edition=

15
00:01:40,091 --> 00:01:43,011
=Episode 11=

16
00:01:44,040 --> 00:01:45,079
They're here.

17
00:01:45,439 --> 00:01:46,040
You can make things clear

18
00:01:46,640 --> 00:01:48,040
in their presence.

19
00:01:51,519 --> 00:01:54,719
Prepare a seat and some tea
for Prime Minister.

20
00:01:55,560 --> 00:01:56,640
Thank you, Your Majesty.

21
00:02:02,079 --> 00:02:03,480
Your Majesty, how about me?

22
00:02:05,799 --> 00:02:06,359
You...

23
00:02:08,120 --> 00:02:09,000
Just stand here.

24
00:02:11,919 --> 00:02:14,599
Your Highness, you don't
need to bow to me.

25
00:02:15,120 --> 00:02:16,840
The Investigator's Office
has checked Lin Gong's body.

26
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:18,960
He was killed by a skilled swordsman
with a fast sword.

27
00:02:19,680 --> 00:02:20,800
Among all swordsmen in the capital city,

28
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:24,439
only Xie Bi'an that works
for the Second Prince

29
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:26,039
has the ability to do that.

30
00:02:26,879 --> 00:02:28,280
Your Highness, you mean...

31
00:02:28,319 --> 00:02:29,280
Your Highness, you mean...

32
00:02:29,280 --> 00:02:31,039
I'm the one who killed Lin Gong.

33
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:34,319
Are you the killer?

34
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:35,919
You have to ask Fan Xian about it.

35
00:02:37,319 --> 00:02:38,000
Your Highness,

36
00:02:38,159 --> 00:02:39,400
how is it related to me?

37
00:02:40,280 --> 00:02:41,879
During 9 a.m. to 11 a.m. of the day
when Lin Gong was killed,

38
00:02:41,879 --> 00:02:43,479
I happened to
meet Fan Xian on the street

39
00:02:43,479 --> 00:02:44,080
and we had a small talk.

40
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:45,719
Xie Bi'an was also there.

41
00:02:46,159 --> 00:02:47,280
I just asked you to be here
to give witness.

42
00:02:48,360 --> 00:02:49,400
Xie Bi'an is known as

43
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:50,879
"Faster than Light."

44
00:02:51,120 --> 00:02:52,000
He is the best swordsman

45
00:02:52,159 --> 00:02:54,159
in the capital city.

46
00:02:54,960 --> 00:02:56,240
Faster than light?

47
00:02:56,560 --> 00:02:57,159
Fast sword.

48
00:02:58,639 --> 00:02:59,280
Is it true?

49
00:03:00,879 --> 00:03:01,719
Yes.

50
00:03:02,039 --> 00:03:03,719
The Investigator's Office has confirmed

51
00:03:04,719 --> 00:03:06,159
Lin Gong was killed
during 9 a.m. to 11 a.m.

52
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:07,960
In this case,

53
00:03:08,039 --> 00:03:10,120
Xie Bi'an didn't have enough time

54
00:03:10,120 --> 00:03:11,680
to rush out of town to do that.

55
00:03:11,759 --> 00:03:12,680
There is another possibility.

56
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:15,159
Fan Xian and you joined hands

57
00:03:15,240 --> 00:03:17,280
to let Xie Bi'an kill Lin Gong.

58
00:03:17,560 --> 00:03:19,639
He was giving false testimony

59
00:03:19,759 --> 00:03:20,599
to help you stay out of it.

60
00:03:20,599 --> 00:03:21,639
It's more ridiculous.

61
00:03:22,960 --> 00:03:24,039
Why did I want to kill Lin Gong?

62
00:03:24,639 --> 00:03:26,159
Why did Fan Xian want to do that?

63
00:03:26,719 --> 00:03:28,919
Lin Gong is the one behind
the assassination attempt on Niulan Street.

64
00:03:29,199 --> 00:03:30,599
Fan Xian holds a grudge against him.

65
00:03:30,879 --> 00:03:31,639
Your Highness,

66
00:03:31,639 --> 00:03:32,879
I have no idea about that.

67
00:03:33,159 --> 00:03:34,560
He's the Crown Prince.

68
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:36,240
We have to bear it
if he wants to declare us guilty.

69
00:03:36,919 --> 00:03:38,080
Then tell me

70
00:03:38,360 --> 00:03:39,919
who else is so skilled at swordsmanship

71
00:03:40,199 --> 00:03:41,560
if it's not Xie Bi'an.

72
00:03:41,719 --> 00:03:42,919
It's not hard

73
00:03:42,919 --> 00:03:43,479
to hire a sword master

74
00:03:43,479 --> 00:03:44,639
who is unrecognized, right?

75
00:03:44,759 --> 00:03:46,080
To whom are you
making pointed allusions?

76
00:03:46,120 --> 00:03:47,319
I'm just trying to reason.

77
00:03:47,599 --> 00:03:48,680
It's enough.

78
00:03:58,719 --> 00:03:59,479
Prime Minister,

79
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:03,280
the victim is your son.
What do you think?

80
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:07,759
In my opinion,

81
00:04:10,199 --> 00:04:11,400
the person to blame

82
00:04:18,040 --> 00:04:19,399
is Chen Pingping.

83
00:04:21,199 --> 00:04:24,800
The Investigator's Office is responsible
for the safety of the capital city.

84
00:04:25,959 --> 00:04:27,759
Up to now, they haven't reported

85
00:04:28,560 --> 00:04:30,199
the truth about my son's death.

86
00:04:31,600 --> 00:04:32,720
It means Chen Pingping

87
00:04:33,360 --> 00:04:36,639
has neglected his duties.

88
00:04:39,199 --> 00:04:40,160
It makes sense.

89
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:45,839
I hope to

90
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:47,680
confront Chen Pingping

91
00:04:48,279 --> 00:04:49,959
and see him be punished
according to law.

92
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:11,759
It seems you enjoy standing there.

93
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:14,279
Your Majesty, shall I kneel down?

94
00:05:16,879 --> 00:05:17,600
Rise.

95
00:05:20,839 --> 00:05:21,480
Pass on my order.

96
00:05:22,720 --> 00:05:24,000
And ask Chen Pingping to come here.

97
00:05:25,399 --> 00:05:26,079
Yes, Your Majesty.

98
00:05:43,560 --> 00:05:44,439
Chen Pingping,

99
00:05:46,519 --> 00:05:47,000
Your Majesty.

100
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:47,839
Do you know your sin?

101
00:05:49,519 --> 00:05:50,439
Why do you say that?

102
00:05:51,160 --> 00:05:52,560
The Prime Minister's son was killed.

103
00:05:53,079 --> 00:05:54,360
As Head of

104
00:05:54,360 --> 00:05:55,199
the Investigator's Office,

105
00:05:55,680 --> 00:05:57,839
you haven't found out
the killer up to now.

106
00:05:58,319 --> 00:05:59,319
You have to take responsibility.

107
00:05:59,879 --> 00:06:00,680
Your Majesty,

108
00:06:02,319 --> 00:06:03,720
we've found out the killer.

109
00:06:05,959 --> 00:06:07,160
You found it out?

110
00:06:08,360 --> 00:06:09,040
Good.

111
00:06:09,680 --> 00:06:13,120
In the presence
of Prime Minister and others,

112
00:06:13,480 --> 00:06:15,160
tell me who is the killer.

113
00:06:23,319 --> 00:06:24,079
Prime Minister,

114
00:06:26,079 --> 00:06:28,399
I'm surprised to hear
the sad news upon my return.

115
00:06:29,240 --> 00:06:31,879
I'm sorry for your loss.

116
00:06:33,240 --> 00:06:34,360
naturally.

117
00:06:37,680 --> 00:06:40,600
Si Gujian from Dongyi Town.

118
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:42,800
One of the Great Masters?

119
00:06:43,040 --> 00:06:43,920
If it were not a Great Master,

120
00:06:44,199 --> 00:06:45,680
who else could use a sword so quickly?

121
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:48,800
As a Great Master,

122
00:06:49,079 --> 00:06:50,879
he travelled hundreds of miles
to the capital city

123
00:06:51,199 --> 00:06:53,120
to kill the Prime Minister's son?

124
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:55,040
Why did he do that?

125
00:06:59,199 --> 00:07:01,360
Lin Gong joined hands with Si Lili

126
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:03,519
to try to assassinate Fan Xian
on Niulan Street,

127
00:07:04,120 --> 00:07:05,439
but Si Gujian lost
a disciple and a follower

128
00:07:05,959 --> 00:07:07,319
during the process.

129
00:07:07,480 --> 00:07:08,759
The two female assassinators

130
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:10,439
were killed by Fan Xian.

131
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:11,680
Why did Si Gujian kill Lin Gong

132
00:07:11,879 --> 00:07:13,160
to take revenge?

133
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:14,720
Everyone knows that

134
00:07:15,160 --> 00:07:17,120
Si Gujian is obsessed
with swordsmanship.

135
00:07:17,720 --> 00:07:18,680
Fan Xian killed the two assassinators

136
00:07:19,360 --> 00:07:21,240
when he was attacked.

137
00:07:21,839 --> 00:07:23,160
Si Gujian would think highly of him

138
00:07:23,160 --> 00:07:24,120
because of his capabilities.

139
00:07:24,480 --> 00:07:26,000
And he'd only take revenge on

140
00:07:26,839 --> 00:07:29,920
Lin Gong and Beiqi

141
00:07:30,240 --> 00:07:33,319
that are behind all this.

142
00:07:33,560 --> 00:07:34,199
Wait!

143
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:37,319
How does it relate to Beiqi?

144
00:07:37,319 --> 00:07:37,839
Your Majesty,

145
00:07:38,399 --> 00:07:41,600
Lin Gong tried to assassinate Fan Xian

146
00:07:41,920 --> 00:07:43,560
because he was fooled by secret agents.

147
00:07:44,120 --> 00:07:47,480
Beiqi disturbed the peace
in the capital city

148
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:48,879
and then got Si Gujian

149
00:07:48,879 --> 00:07:49,600
involved into this case.

150
00:07:49,720 --> 00:07:51,879
They're really evil-minded.

151
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:55,079
Your Majesty, please dispatch troops

152
00:07:55,920 --> 00:07:57,920
and go on a punitive expedition
against Beiqi.

153
00:07:58,920 --> 00:08:01,360
What? Dispatch troops?

154
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:02,439
To revolt?

155
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:09,759
To revolt?

156
00:08:13,199 --> 00:08:14,519
We can't do that
without careful thought.

157
00:08:21,160 --> 00:08:24,480
Prime Minister, what do you think?

158
00:08:28,720 --> 00:08:29,240
Prime Minister.

159
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:34,600
Your Majesty,

160
00:08:35,240 --> 00:08:37,120
I beg you to bring fair back

161
00:08:38,039 --> 00:08:39,399
to my dead son.

162
00:08:39,399 --> 00:08:41,080
Prime Minister, you're
the most important official.

163
00:08:41,399 --> 00:08:42,279
Come on. Rise.

164
00:08:42,279 --> 00:08:44,279
Your Majesty,

165
00:08:44,639 --> 00:08:46,360
I beg you to bring fair back

166
00:08:46,879 --> 00:08:49,120
to my dead son!

167
00:09:00,279 --> 00:09:03,039
In this case, I'll order

168
00:09:03,519 --> 00:09:06,080
Dongyi Town to hand over the killer.

169
00:09:09,080 --> 00:09:11,200
As for Beiqi...

170
00:09:12,759 --> 00:09:13,919
Beiqi?

171
00:09:15,279 --> 00:09:17,279
getting into a fight with them,

172
00:09:17,600 --> 00:09:19,440
but they've gone too far in bullying us.

173
00:09:19,720 --> 00:09:20,799
They're pressing on step by step.

174
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:22,279
So,

175
00:09:25,399 --> 00:09:26,480
let's go to war.

176
00:09:32,960 --> 00:09:35,120
I'll take a nation's strength

177
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:37,480
to punish the wicked.

178
00:09:41,360 --> 00:09:46,080
I see.

179
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:50,080
I see.

180
00:09:50,240 --> 00:09:52,919
Everything is clear now.

181
00:09:53,879 --> 00:09:54,279
You...

182
00:09:55,519 --> 00:09:56,039
Your Majesty.

183
00:09:56,399 --> 00:09:57,559
You slandered your brother,

184
00:09:57,919 --> 00:09:59,600
so you'll be grounded for three days.

185
00:09:59,799 --> 00:10:00,879
Read more classics.

186
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:01,919
Both of you can leave.

187
00:10:11,080 --> 00:10:12,080
Your Highness,

188
00:10:18,519 --> 00:10:19,240
As brothers,

189
00:10:19,240 --> 00:10:20,759
we haven't had
a heart-to-heart talk for long.

190
00:10:20,759 --> 00:10:23,440
How about getting together someday?

191
00:10:25,080 --> 00:10:27,600
I'll be grounded for three days.
I don't dare to disobey the order.

192
00:10:39,919 --> 00:10:40,559
Prime Minister,

193
00:10:42,480 --> 00:10:43,720
you lost your son.

194
00:10:43,720 --> 00:10:45,440
I understand how you're feeling,

195
00:10:45,679 --> 00:10:47,720
but the war is going to start.

196
00:10:48,440 --> 00:10:49,759
You have to take good care of yourself.

197
00:10:49,879 --> 00:10:51,440
The six ministries need your management.

198
00:10:52,480 --> 00:10:53,399
I have

199
00:10:55,559 --> 00:10:57,960
mixed feelings

200
00:11:00,320 --> 00:11:01,679
that are beyond words.

201
00:11:02,840 --> 00:11:05,080
It's okay as long
as it's clear in your mind.

202
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:06,720
Your Majesty.

203
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:09,919
I have one more request.

204
00:11:10,120 --> 00:11:10,759
Go ahead.

205
00:11:11,840 --> 00:11:14,879
Now that the whole thing came to light,

206
00:11:16,519 --> 00:11:17,960
I hope Head Chen

207
00:11:19,120 --> 00:11:20,759
can have my son's body

208
00:11:21,799 --> 00:11:23,600
sent to my mansion.

209
00:11:24,919 --> 00:11:26,639
He made a big mistake,

210
00:11:27,720 --> 00:11:29,559
but he's my son, anyway.

211
00:11:31,039 --> 00:11:35,320
I want to have his bones buried.

212
00:11:36,240 --> 00:11:37,559
It's only right and proper.

213
00:11:39,519 --> 00:11:40,639
I'll have him

214
00:11:41,279 --> 00:11:43,879
sent back later.

215
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:50,559
In this case, your subordinate
takes his leave.

216
00:11:52,440 --> 00:11:52,919
Prime Minister.

217
00:11:57,600 --> 00:11:58,279
Prime Minister,

218
00:11:59,480 --> 00:12:01,159
considering what happened
between your son and Fan Xian,

219
00:12:01,159 --> 00:12:02,200
Your Majesty, it seems that

220
00:12:03,399 --> 00:12:05,360
invalidate Wan'er's marriage contract

221
00:12:07,279 --> 00:12:08,720
to Fan Xian?

222
00:12:09,039 --> 00:12:13,320
It's my son that made a mistake.
It has nothing to do with Fan Xian.

223
00:12:14,639 --> 00:12:17,679
Besides, Fan Xian did a lot

224
00:12:18,720 --> 00:12:21,080
to chase secret agents of Beiqi.

225
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:23,200
We don't need to

226
00:12:25,159 --> 00:12:26,240
invalidate their marriage contract.

227
00:12:26,919 --> 00:12:28,000
You lost your son.

228
00:12:28,279 --> 00:12:29,360
According to etiquette,

229
00:12:29,360 --> 00:12:31,600
no wedding ceremonies should be
held in three years in your mansion.

230
00:12:31,879 --> 00:12:32,559
Wan'er.

231
00:12:33,440 --> 00:12:35,600
has nothing to the Lin mansion in name.

232
00:12:36,519 --> 00:12:37,639
They can get married

233
00:12:37,639 --> 00:12:39,120
as scheduled.

234
00:12:39,639 --> 00:12:41,919
Right. It makes sense.

235
00:12:42,519 --> 00:12:44,159
Their marriage contract
will remain unchanged.

236
00:12:44,799 --> 00:12:46,120
But the war is going to begin,

237
00:12:46,679 --> 00:12:47,759
so let's talk
about their wedding ceremony

238
00:12:48,360 --> 00:12:51,039
after the war ends.

239
00:12:53,759 --> 00:12:54,960
Your Majesty, it's a wise decision.

240
00:12:55,639 --> 00:12:56,720
See Prime Minister out.

241
00:12:58,320 --> 00:13:00,039
Your Majesty, I'm leaving too.

242
00:13:01,120 --> 00:13:01,840
You're still here?

243
00:13:02,039 --> 00:13:02,519
Yes.

244
00:13:02,879 --> 00:13:03,240
Okay.

245
00:13:18,840 --> 00:13:19,919
Eunuch Hou, don't bother.

246
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:21,320
We'll leave by ourselves.

247
00:13:22,080 --> 00:13:24,519
I'd better see you out.

248
00:13:34,200 --> 00:13:34,639
Let's go.

249
00:13:40,799 --> 00:13:42,679
Si Gujian killed Lin Gong?

250
00:13:46,600 --> 00:13:48,559
It's ridiculous.

251
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:50,120
It's true that Lin Gong was killed

252
00:13:50,759 --> 00:13:52,200
by a skilled swordsman.

253
00:13:52,440 --> 00:13:54,039
Do you think Lin Ruofu bought the story?

254
00:13:57,240 --> 00:13:59,000
It doesn't matter as long
as the common people are convinced.

255
00:14:03,480 --> 00:14:04,360
Did you

256
00:14:04,879 --> 00:14:06,399
really see the Second Prince

257
00:14:06,399 --> 00:14:07,399
and Xie Bi'an that day?

258
00:14:08,440 --> 00:14:09,279
Yes, I did.

259
00:14:10,679 --> 00:14:12,720
Then the Second Prince
couldn't have done that.

260
00:14:14,200 --> 00:14:15,519
Isn't it Si Gujian?

261
00:14:16,120 --> 00:14:17,720
Did a Great Master come here

262
00:14:17,720 --> 00:14:19,399
to kill Gong'er

263
00:14:19,840 --> 00:14:21,679
just for his two unknown followers?

264
00:14:23,240 --> 00:14:24,080
Uncle, you don't believe that?

265
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:27,840
I'm not stupid.

266
00:14:28,240 --> 00:14:29,399
In this case,

267
00:14:29,600 --> 00:14:30,519
why didn't you say it out?

268
00:14:37,919 --> 00:14:41,080
His Majesty acted in concert
with Chen Pingping

269
00:14:41,559 --> 00:14:43,279
just to draw a final decision.

270
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:46,039
Nobody cares if I believe it or not.

271
00:14:47,080 --> 00:14:48,480
Is it the answer His Majesty wants?

272
00:14:50,639 --> 00:14:53,000
It's the answer Nanqing wants.

273
00:14:53,919 --> 00:14:56,480
It'll be used as a perfect excuse

274
00:14:57,159 --> 00:14:58,559
to send armed forces to attack Beiqi.

275
00:15:00,240 --> 00:15:04,679
The common people will be filled
with a common hatred.

276
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:09,639
What a good answer!

277
00:15:12,200 --> 00:15:14,000
How about the truth
about Lin Gong's death?

278
